description:
It was first thought that Sh2-174 was a planetary nebula associated with the white dwarf GD 561, even though this star was significantly offset from the centre of the nebula.  A later opposing view was that Sh2-174 was a Strömgren Sphere (or zone) - a sphere of ionized hydrogen in the interstellar medium surrounding a young hot star.   It is possible that Sh2-174 represents some sort of combination of planetary nebula and Strömgren sphere [see Ransom et al (2015) Astrophysical Journal 799:198].

Sh2-174 was photographed between 2 and 12 June 2021 from our widefield imaging rig in Spain.  Capture details are as follows:

Telescope: Takahashi FSQ 106
Camera: QSI 683
Filters: Astrodon
Mount: 10 Micron GM1000HPS

Ha: 19 x 1200s
OIII: 24 x 1200s
Red: 36 x 300s
Green: 36 x 300s
Blue: 36 x 300s

A total of 23 hours and 20 minutes exposure.

Data: Steve Milne & Barry Wilson
Processing: Steve Milne
title: Sharpless 2-174 in Cepheus
